VAs part of the traditional concert series, Nada Bharati featured Duddu Radhika, former disciple of Raghava Chari of Hyderbad Brothers duo.Radhika began her concert with a Kambhojiatatala varnamSarasijanabhaand went forSwaminatha Paripalayain Nata of Deekshitar which was impressive withswaramevolving in interesting patterns.Sriranjani was then elaborated forMarubalkaof Thayagaraja with a briefswarakalpana.Bhogendra sayeenamin Kuntalavarali of Swathi Thirunal was a fast number.The majorragaof the concert was Thodi which was essayed well.Dachukovalenaof Thyagaraja was her chosenkritiin thisraga. Theswarakalpanawas good. Thekritirendition should have been in Vilambakalam instead ofmadhyama kalashe sang in. The other important traditional number wasragam-tanam-pallaviin Shanmukhapriya.Theragawas neatly expanded scaling to upper octaves, while thetanamwas brief but sweet. The line she sang forpallaviwasNee Padamule Gathiyani Nammithi Sree Rama Chandra.Theswaraprathsrain it was also neat. Radhika concluded with ajawaliandtarangam.Rajan on violin lent reasonably good support. Srinivas Gopalan was on mridangam and histani avartanamwas a commendable presentation.
